Google.text:
First, let me note that for the past 6 years, I have dined here roughly 4 times each year. Mostly, I been very pleased with everything. Last night, I ordered takeout in order to relax and dine at home. Online, I ordered my standby Thai comfort dish of Basil Sauce with a side of brown rice. I arrived at the Pine Ridge location to find the dinner rush had passed and 4 tables inside and 5 outside had diners. There were 3 servers and a kitchen staff of who knows how many but at least 3 different faces appeared at the small counter where servers pickup meals from the kitchen.

While not busy, no employee made eye contact much less saying hello and or offering a "Someone will be with you shortly" greeting or whatever. With 2 other takeout customers there before me I joined their queue near a table laden with food in containers but none of it was going anywhere. More takeout containers came out of the kitchen and were placed on the table. After being there for at least 15 minutes with still no acknowledgement of my presence by anyone who worked there, one server/hostess came over to the table, sat down, spread out 6 take-out order receipts, starting reading them and sorted through the 15 or more containers on the able  to match each item to the proper printed receipt. No receipt had a complete order so the server got up and performed some other tasks. Meanwhile, a new take-out customer who ordered online and was completely ignored. All the while, the take-out food is cooling.
More food came out of the kitchen and was put on the table by the server/hostess and more receipts were read and containers were matched to an order. Finally, one of the customers there before  me had a complete order, paid and left. My term came next except, the side of brown rice still wasn't ready. It was forgotten. The server/hostess went to the kitchen and brought back the brown rice. I should have opened every container and checked it personally before paying but I didn't. My big mistake. Whatever sauce I was given was far different from the usual, it was not spiced properly but I added my own chili pepper sauce at home. The basil used was not fresh but dried out stems and fibrous. The brown rice was a glutinous mass of rice mush so overcooked and dried out and cold that the scoop of rice was glued together and there were no individual rice grains separable from the mass, just different degrees of textured mush. Disgusting.

Will I go back again. Maybe, but only as a last resort as there are other Thai restaurants in the area. Oh well, every meal is an adventure. Sometimes they end really well and other times ...

Komoon used to be one of my favorite restaurants, unfortunately as they've expanded the quality of service and food has gone way down, especially with my most recent experience.

I received an email for a promotion for either 20% off any order or 50% if you spend at least $50. I decided to bring a couple of my colleagues who had never been and I had hyped them up about how good the food was. We got a bunch of appetizers and I got the basil chicken with rice (a dish I used to always get) for my entree but the taste was just not good. Sauce was very sweet, seems like they may have changed the recipe. Although the food was not great, I was still having a good experience. That was until I mentioned the coupon.. Our server said we were not eligible for the coupon as it was only allowed to be used for dinner service. However, no where in the email is this stated. The only small print mentioned that the 20% off any order or 50% off $50 can not be combined. Even if this was their intention (only having the coupon for dinner) a well run restaurant would still honor the coupon and update the email for future guests. However, this was not done. She did end up calling a manager who gave us 20% off our order but in my opinion this is still not the right thing to do. When I was younger, I worked in the service industry for years and understand how the treat customers. I hope Komoon learns from this experience but for the time being I will not be recommending or returning to their restaurants. I hope your experience is better than mine.
